Ford Motor Co said it awarded 164.3 mlndlrs in bonuses to 5,528 executives based on the company'srecord 3.3 billion dlrs in 1986 profits.    The number two U.S. automaker said chairman Donald Petersenlast year collected more than 4.3 mln dlrs, inlcuing salary of660,772 dlrs, a 1.3 mln dlr bonus and nearly 2.4 mln dlrs fromexercising stock options.    Ford said each of it five top executives received bonuseswhich swelled their pay last year past the one mln dlr mark.    Ford said it last month paid 371 mln dlrs in profit-sharingto 160,000 hourly and salaried employees in the U.S.    The company also disclosed in its proxy statement mailed to262,000 shareholders for Ford's May 14 annual meeting inDetroit that directors John Connally and Carter Burgess areretiring from its board and that Irvine Hockaday Jr, presidentof Hallmark Cards Inc of Kansas City, Mo, is being nominatedfor a board seat. Reuter&#3;